<p><img alt="Many busy people sitting at desks." class="right" src="/images/upload/images/library/library4719.jpg" style="height:234px; margin-bottom:16px; margin-top:16px; width:350px" /></p>

<p><br />
Named for the Reverend Monsignor A. P. Mahoney, Rector of the Seminary from 1930 to 1966, the&nbsp; library supports teaching and learning in the theology and philosophy programmes. Eight <a href="/images/upload/files/Guiding%20Principles%20.pdf">Guiding Principles</a> inform our work. The library&rsquo;s strength includes its extensive scripture collection, Roman Catholic theology, patristics, canon law and Thomistic materials.&nbsp; The collection can be accessed through the Shared Library Catalogue which comprises the holdings of <a href="http://www.lib.uwo.ca" target="_blank">Western Libraries</a> and the Affiliate University College Libraries (<a href="http://brescia.uwo.ca/library/" target="_blank">Brescia</a>, <a href="http://huronuc.libguides.com/home" target="_blank">Huron</a>, and <a href="http://www.kings.uwo.ca/library/" target="_blank">King&#39;s</a>).</p>

<p><a href="http://www.stpetersseminary.ca/Resources/Seminary-Archives/38">The Michael R. Prieur Seminary Archives</a> are located within the library on the lower level.&nbsp;</p>

<p>The A. P. Mahoney Library hosts an <em><strong><a href="http://www.stpetersseminary.ca/Library/Lectures/82">annual lecture</a></strong></em> to celebrate Theological Libraries Month, an initiative of the American Theological Library Association, held in October of each year. The lecture serves as a vehicle to showcase the seminary&rsquo;s talented faculty and is followed by a reception in the library.&nbsp;The&nbsp;lecture is held in the St. Joseph Auditorium on the Wednesday evening following the Thanksgiving holiday.&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
                                        
